cs.EC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.CR

The paper discusses the Web economy and its participants, which involves economic concepts such as incentives, transactions, and properties. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The paper also discusses the impact and scale of the Web, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also mentions the need for the Web to be secure and reliable, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
